# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the ComercioPlus React application.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:

1. **src/app/App.tsx**
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component after the `<Routes>` component within the `<BrowserRouter>` wrapper
   - This provides seamless integration with React Router for automatic route tracking

2. **package.json**
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` dependency (version ^1.6.1)
   - The package was installed using npm to ensure compatibility with the existing project setup

3. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated with the new @vercel/analytics package and its dependencies
   - 269 new packages added to support the analytics functionality

## Implementation Details

Following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications:
- Used the `@vercel/analytics/react` package which provides React-specific integration
- Placed the Analytics component at the root level of the app (in App.tsx) to ensure it tracks all page views across all routes
- The component automatically detects route changes when using react-router-dom

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ Dependencies installed successfully using `npm install @vercel/analytics`
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter passed with no issues (`npm run lint`)
